oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Miser, Frank
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: QUESTION: I have a problem with myParrakeet spitting up, is there a cure?Answer: Birds commonly sp1t up food fortwo main reasons. The fust is a very naturalactivity of a young male enteringadulthood, trying to feed a toy or mirrorin lieu of a female or baby. The onlyremedy is to remove the toy or mirrorand hope the bird does not lavish hisaffection on still another substitute. Thisis not a dangerous situation and will stopat the end of the cycle.
